reviews_data.review_text: So far a good addition to the MP neighborhood. Had a nice breakfast burrito, but some of the other food items could be less greasy like the pizza and smash burgers. Judging by the crowd the lighter the better.
Great quality in a great location! Love the local partnerships
Love this place. Been a customer since their location on East Blvd in Dilworth. Followed them to Elizabeth, but SO happy they opened a location in Myers Park!

reviews_data.review_text: Very cute location! Spacious patio and family/dog friendly. The food was excellent and their drinks were particurarly delicious. I will be back soon!

Love the new location! Our favorites are the chicken avocado wrap, hipster salad (I like to add shrimp), and my husband is a big fan of the burger! Super kid friendly with chicken tenders - possibly the best in Charlotte. Highly recommend adding it to your local routine.

Elizabeth Location Only - (since they fail to respond to customer’s concerns) I guess the only way to reach this place is to leave a one star review. I’ve tried calling, messaging on IG and the contact tab on your website and still no response. On last Friday, I paid for two orders of kids chicken tenders between 3:00-3:30 via an online order. The chicken tenders were not edible and basically burnt. All I want is my money back for the meal that I paid for. If someone could actually respond to a customer’s request that would be nice.
I checked this new location out over the weekend! The service and atmosphere were great! So happy they are finally open! Natalie was wonderful!

Visited People’s Market on 6/8, just one week into them being open. The space is very cute and has ample seating inside and outside. I ordered the Market Bagel and it was DELICIOUS. I also got a plain cold brew and it was very good. My partner got Peoples Market Platter and thought the bacon was a standout. Can’t wait to come back for a different meal time!
